race.comment: BEREZKA (2) is a consistent mare but hasn't won for 72 weeks. Boxed on well to get up for third last start over 1250m at Canterbury. Raced well last prep in Brisbane in better races than this. Just needs luck from a sticky gate to break the win drought. TILL DUSK (11) worked home well but found one better when fresh from a seven-month spell over 1200m at this track last start, the first appearance since transferring from Victoria. Won second-up last prep at Sale. Sparingly raced mare who is a serious threat. THE STARS (9) stayed at 1200m for her second-up run recently and was just even through the line in third place. Perfectly drawn and looks ready to get out to this distance for the first time. DIVINE DIAMONDS (12) weakened late when resuming over 1200m here last start. Second-up form is far better and this is her pet trip. Can improve sharply.
